## 1.5.4 (2016-10-12)

* Fix activation on Atom 1.11.

## 1.5.3 (2016-06-21)

* Fix positioning of other modal panes in One Dark/Light themes.

## 1.5.2 (2016-06-19)

* Fix centering of tab list under the One Dark/Light themes.

## 1.5.1 (2016-06-16)

* Fix error when removing a tab with "reorder tabs" option set.

## 1.5.0 (2016-06-13)

* Load the package on startup, so tabs are tracked correctly before first use.
* Fix selected item jumping unexpectedly when cursor is over the tab list.

## 1.4.0 (2016-04-20)

* Works with Atom 1.7.
* Fix potential error on loading due to some missing serialized state.
* Add setting to reorder tabs to match the list. [Ezequiel Schwartzman]

## 1.3.3 (2015-12-02)

* Update tab list when file is renamed.
* Fix icons & directory name in tab list under recent Atom versions.
* Fix tab list jumping around when scrolling through a long tab list under the
  mouse cursor.

## 1.3.2 (2015-10-14)

* Fix error when invoking the switcher with no tabs open.

## 1.3.1 (2015-09-20)

* Fix potential error when disabling the package.

## 1.3.0 (2015-09-16)

* Wait a (configurable) moment before displaying tab list. [Eldar Gabdullin]
* MRU tab is now focused after closing a tab.
* Tab list now scrolls when moving up/down via keyboard.

## 1.2.1 (2015-07-01)

* Fix tab list appearing when a tab is closed.
* Clicking outside the tab list (even another window) now cancels the switch.

## 1.2.0 (2015-06-30)

* You can now select tabs in the list with the mouse.
* alt-s saves files from the tab list.
* alt-w closes tabs from the tab list.
* Better directory names in tab list when multiple project folders are used.
  [Eldar Gabdullin]

## 1.1.1 (2015-06-27)

* Fix list styling in certain scenarios.

## 1.1.0 (2015-06-24)

* Tab list order is persisted across editor sessions.
* Tab list scrolls as needed.

## 1.0.1 (2015-06-18)

* Fix styling issues with One and Light UI themes.

## 1.0.0 (2015-06-15)

* Witch-inspired tab menu (install file-icons package for icons).
* Don't change order of tabs in the tab bar.
* Instead use `alt-[` and `alt-]` to change tabs via the menu.

## 0.4.0 (2015-06-07)

* Move tab when modifiers are released, instead of using a 1 second timeout.

## 0.3.0 (2015-06-07)

* We're back! Support for Atom 0.207.

## 0.2.0 (2014-03-15)

* Consider a tab recently used whenever it was activated, not just when our
  tab-switching commands were used. We no longer define tab-switching commands.
